{
  "id": "019d287b-38bd-7ef2-a390-5ff458cdf302",
  "content": "## Cross-Batch spawned_by Edge Resolution — Implementation\n\nAdded `get_by_source_version(scope_id, source_version) -> Option<KnowledgeEntry>` to the `QueryableStore` trait for looking up entries by their source_version string within a scope.\n\n### LiteStore Implementation\n- New Redb secondary index: `SOURCE_VERSION_INDEX` keyed by `\"{scope_id}:{source_version}\" -> uuid_str`\n- Populated during `index_entry()` (insert path) and `rebuild_from_files()`\n- Cleaned up during `delete_scope()` via range scan\n- Empty source_versions are skipped (not indexed, return None on lookup)\n\n### PostgresStore Implementation\n- Simple `WHERE scope_id = $1 AND source_version = $2 LIMIT 1` query\n- Added composite index `idx_knowledge_source_version ON knowledge(scope_id, source_version)` in init_schema\n\n### workspace.rs Cross-Batch Resolution\n- When parent session not in current batch, constructs `\"{parent_sid}:turn-1\"` and queries `get_by_source_version` on user-history scope\n- Three outcomes handled: found (create edge), not found (log note), error (log warning)\n\n### Known Limitations\n- Key separator `:` is shared with source_version format — low collision risk since scope_ids are controlled strings\n- No retry/backfill if child ingested before parent (edge permanently skipped)\n- `LIMIT 1` / last-write-wins on duplicate source_versions (acceptable for session-history use case)",
  "source_version": "mcp",
  "scope_id": "corvia",
